link":null,"contributor":false,"short_title":"Obama's Executive Action on Immigration Will Tear Us Apart","hero":{"class":"landscape","thumbnail":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/11\/171435251.jpg?w=100&h=100&crop=1","src":{"small":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/11\/171435251.jpg?w=280&h=187&crop=1","small_2x":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/11\/171435251.jpg?w=560&h=374&crop=1","large":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/11\/171435251.jpg?w=550&h=367&crop=1","large_2x":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/11\/171435251.jpg?w=1100&h=734&crop=1"},"credit":"MANDEL NGAN&mdash;AFP\/Getty Images","caption":"President Barack Obama meets with business leaders on immigration reform on June 24, 2013 in the Roosevelt Room of the White House in Washington, DC. ","alt":"US-POLITICS-IMMIGRATION-OBAMA","providers":[]}},{"id":3596143,"title":"Univision's Jorge Ramos Calls Obama's Immigration Actions a 'Triumph For The Latino Community'","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3596143\/immigration-jorge-ramos-univision\/","format":"article","paid":false,"edit_link":null,"contributor":false,"short_title":"Univision's Jorge Ramos Calls Obama's Immigration Actions a 'Triumph For The Latino Community'"}],"subjects":[null],"ads":{"neg":"false","post_title":"Is Obama Overreaching on Immigration? Lincoln and FDR Would Say 'No'"},"Partner_Module":{"partner":"Select","post_title":"Is Obama Overreaching on Immigration? Lincoln and FDR Would Say 'No'"},"email_title":"Is%20Obama%20Overreaching%20on%20Immigration%3F%20Lincoln%20and%20FDR%20Would%20Say%20%E2%80%98No%E2%80%99%20%7C%20TIME","email_body":"Is%20Obama%20Overreaching%20on%20Immigration%3F%20Lincoln%20and%20FDR%20Would%20Say%20%E2%80%98No%E2%80%99%0A%0ALike%20Lincoln%20and%20Roosevelt%20before%20him%2C%20Obama%20occupies%20the%20White%20House%20in%20a%20time%20of%20great%20crisis%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3598069%2Fobama-immigration-lincoln-fdr%2F","omniture":{"modules":"rr-related|rr-partner|rr-mag|rr-ad|rr-share"},"outbrain":{"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3598069\/obama-immigration-lincoln-fdr\/","widget_id":"AR_6","hide":false}},{"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3583782\/hot-air-balloon-history\/","shortlink":"http:\/\/wp.me\/p5HMd-f2iW","title":"A Sheep, a Duck and a Rooster in a Hot-Air Balloon \u2014 No Joke","friendly_title":"A Sheep, a Duck and a Rooster in a Hot-Air Balloon \u2014 No Joke","post_type":"post","available":true,"time_article":true,"comments_allowed":true,"short_title":"A Sheep, a Duck and a Rooster in a Hot-Air Balloon \u2014 No Joke","excerpt":"Nov. 21, 1783: Two men take flight over Paris on the world\u2019s first untethered hot-air balloon ride","format":"article","time":{"pretty":"Nov. 21, 2014","published":"2014-11-21 07:30:30","updated":"2014-11-21 12:30:30","minute":"7:30 am","short":"11\/21"},"authors":[{"id":262496150,"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/author\/jennifer-latson\/","name":"Jennifer Latson","bio":"","short_bio":"","types":["contributor"],"twitter":"JennieLatson","twitter_url":"https:\/\/twitter.com\/JennieLatson","gplus":"","fb":"","email":"","thumbnail":null,"contributor":false}],"content":"<aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-related\" data-name=\"rr-related\"><div class=\"read-more-inline related\"><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3551643\/virgin-crash-branson-amateur\/\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-video data-event=\"rr-related\"><img src=\"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/10\/virgin-spaceshiptwo.jpg?w=560&#038;h=374&#038;crop=1\" alt=\"End of the line: Wreckage from Virgin Galactic&#039;s SpaceShipTwo is shown in this still image captured from KNBC video footage from Mojave, California on Oct. 31, 2014.\" title=\"End of the line: Wreckage from Virgin Galactic&#039;s SpaceShipTwo is shown in this still image captured from KNBC video footage from Mojave, California on Oct. 31, 2014. \"><h6 class=\"read-more-list-h\">More<\/h6><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title\">Enough With Amateur-Hour Space Flight<\/h3><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3531854\/cheap-thanksgiving-airfare\/\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-article data-event=\"rr-related\"><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title\">The Secret to Getting a Ridiculously Cheap Thanksgiving Flight<\/h3><\/a><\/div><\/aside><p>Before subjecting humans to the unknown dangers of flight in a hot-air balloon, French inventors conducted a trial run, sending a sheep, a duck and a rooster up in the air over Versailles.<\/p>\n<aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-partner\" data-name=\"rr-partner\"><div class=\"read-more-list\"><h6 class=\"read-more-list-h\">More<\/h6><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3595882\/bank-industry-dishonesty-study\/\" class=\"read-more-list-article\" data-event=\"rr-more\">Study Suggests Banking Industry Breeds Dishonesty<\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3594928\/best-american-science-nature-writing-2014\/\" class=\"read-more-list-article\" data-event=\"rr-more\">Sorting Fact From Fiction and What the Best Science Writing Can Teach Us<\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/storyline\/michael-brown-shooting\/pair-suspected-trying-acquire-bombs-ferguson-protests-n254021?cid=par-time_20141122\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">Feds Suspect Pair Sought Bombs for Ferguson Protests <span>NBC News<\/span><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/news\/crime-courts\/ohio-men-wrongly-convicted-murder-after-39-years-released-n253356?cid=par-time_20141122\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">Two Ohio Men Wrongly Convicted of Murder Walk Free <span>NBC News<\/span><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/news\/us-news\/fsu-shooter-myron-may-left-message-i-do-not-want-n253436?cid=par-time_20141122\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">FSU Shooter Left Message: 'I Do Not Want to Die in Vain' <span>NBC News<\/span><\/a><\/div><\/aside><p>Anyone who was anyone in pre-revolution France came out for the September 1783 demonstration in the courtyard of the royal palace. According to Simon Schama, the author of <a href=\"http:\/\/www.amazon.com\/Citizens-A-Chronicle-French-Revolution\/dp\/0679726101\"><em>Citizens: A Chronicle of the French Revolution<\/em><\/a><em>,<\/em> the spectators included King Louis XVI, his wife Marie Antoinette and 130,000 French citizens who, six years before returning to the palace to riot over the scarcity of bread, were drawn by sheer curiosity over how the animals would fare in the balloon&rsquo;s basket.<\/p>\n<p>The eight-minute flight, which ended in the woods a few miles from the palace, didn&rsquo;t seem to do the barnyard trio any harm, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.amazon.com\/Citizens-A-Chronicle-French-Revolution\/dp\/0679726101\">Schama writes<\/a>: &ldquo;&lsquo;It was judged that they had not suffered,&rsquo; ran one press comment, &lsquo;but they were, to say the least, much astonished.&rsquo;&rdquo;<\/p>\n<p>The public was similarly astonished when, on this day, Nov. 21, two months after the sheep and fowl made their historic trip, two eminent Frenchmen went aloft themselves in the world&rsquo;s first untethered hot-air balloon ride.<\/p>\n<p>Jean-Fran&ccedil;ois Pil&acirc;tre de Rozier, a chemistry and physics teacher, and the Marquis d&rsquo;Arlandes, a military officer, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.space.com\/16595-montgolfiers-first-balloon-flight.html\">flew nearly six miles, from the center of Paris to the suburbs, in 25 minutes<\/a>. This time, Benjamin Franklin was among the spectators, according to Space.com. He later marveled in his journal about the experience, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.space.com\/16595-montgolfiers-first-balloon-flight.html\">writing<\/a>, &ldquo;We observed [the balloon] lift off in the most majestic manner. When it reached around 250 feet in altitude, the intrepid voyagers lowered their hats to salute the spectators. We could not help feeling a certain mixture of awe and admiration.&rdquo;<\/p><div class=\"content-ad\" id=\"content-ad-3583782\"><\/div>\n<p>It was more than a century before the Wright brothers lifted the first powered airplane off the ground in 1903, and more than two centuries before another pair &mdash; <a href=\"http:\/\/content.time.com\/time\/subscriber\/article\/0,33009,990550,00.html\">a Swiss psychiatrist and a British balloon instructor<\/a> &mdash; circumnavigated the globe in an air balloon in a record-breaking 20 days. This first balloon, rather delicately constructed of paper and silk, and <a href=\"http:\/\/www.aps.org\/publications\/apsnews\/200611\/history.cfm\">requiring a large supply of fuel<\/a> to stoke the fire that kept it aloft (but also threatened to burn it down), likely wouldn&rsquo;t have made it so far.<\/p>\n<p>There were still a few bugs to work out in this novel form of flight. The inventors themselves <a href=\"http:\/\/www.aps.org\/publications\/apsnews\/200611\/history.cfm\">didn&rsquo;t quite grasp the physics<\/a> that made the balloon rise, believing that they had discovered a new kind of gas that was lighter than air. In fact, the gas <em>was <\/em>air, just hotter and therefore lighter than the air surrounding it.<\/p>\n<p>Experimenting with different gases ultimately led to the demise of one of the intrepid voyagers aboard the first balloon flight. Pil&acirc;tre de Rozier was killed two years later while attempting to cross the English Channel in a balloon powered by hydrogen and hot air, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.space.com\/16595-montgolfiers-first-balloon-flight.html\">which exploded<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><em><strong>Read about the 1999 balloon trip around the world, here in the TIME Vault<\/strong><\/em>: <a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/vault\/issue\/1999-03-29\/page\/41\/\" target=\"_blank\">Around the World in a Balloon in 20 Days<\/a><\/p><aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-ad\" data-name=\"rr-ad\"><div class=\"right-rail-ad\" id=\"right-rail-ad-3583782\"><\/div><\/aside><aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-share\" data-name=\"rr-share\"><span class=\"social-links\">\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-mail social-link-mail\" href=\"mailto:?subject=A%20Sheep%2C%20a%20Duck%20and%20a%20Rooster%20in%20a%20Hot-Air%20Balloon%20%E2%80%94%20No%20Joke%20%7C%20TIME&body=A%20Sheep%2C%20a%20Duck%20and%20a%20Rooster%20in%20a%20Hot-Air%20Balloon%20%E2%80%94%20No%20Joke%0A%0ANov.%2021%2C%201783%3A%20Two%20men%20take%20flight%20over%20Paris%20on%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20untethered%20hot-air%20balloon%20ride%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3583782%2Fhot-air-balloon-history%2F\" data-event=\"email\" title=\"Click to Email this article\"><\/a>\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-fb social-link-fb popup\" href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/sharer\/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3583782%2Fhot-air-balloon-history%2F\" data-event=\"fb-share\" title=\"Click to post this article to Facebook\"><\/a>\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-tw social-link-tw popup\" href=\"#\" data-href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwp.me%2Fp5HMd-f2iW&text=Nov.%2021%2C%201783%3A%20Two%20men%20take%20flight%20over%20Paris%20on%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20untethered%20hot-air%20balloon%20ride&via=TIMEHistory\" data-event=\"tweet\" title=\"Click to Tweet this article\"><\/a>\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-linkedin social-link-linkedin popup\" href=\"http:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/shareArticle?mini=true&url=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3583782%2Fhot-air-balloon-history%2F&title=A+Sheep%2C+a+Duck+and+a+Rooster+in+a+Hot-Air+Balloon+%E2%80%94+No+Joke\" data-event=\"linkedin\" title=\"Click to post this article to LinkedIn\"><\/a>\n    <a href=\"#\" class=\"time-icons time-icons-comment toggle-comments\" data-lf-site-id=\"314099\" data-lf-article-id=\"3583782\" data-url=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3583782\/hot-air-balloon-history\/\" data-title=\"A Sheep, a Duck and a Rooster in a Hot-Air Balloon \u2014 No Joke\" title=\"Click to view and post comments\" data-event=\"comment-