/i> (1996)","alt":"","providers":[]}},{"id":3597091,"title":"Mike Nichols Dies at Age 83","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3597091\/mike-nichols-dead\/","format":"video","paid":false,"edit_link":null,"contributor":false,"short_title":"Mike Nichols Dies at 83"}],"subjects":[null],"ads":{"neg":"false","post_title":"Mike Nichols: A Half-Century of Raves"},"Partner_Module":{"partner":"Select","post_title":"Mike Nichols: A Half-Century of Raves"},"email_title":"Mike%20Nichols%3A%20A%20Half-Century%20of%20Raves%20%7C%20TIME","email_body":"Mike%20Nichols%3A%20A%20Half-Century%20of%20Raves%0A%0AHe%20was%20%27the%20sort%20of%20director%20whom%20most%20writers%20and%20actors%20only%20meet%20when%20they%20are%20asleep%20and%20dreaming%27%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3597404%2Fmike-nichols%2F","omniture":{"modules":"rr-related|rr-partner|rr-ad|rr-share"},"outbrain":{"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3597404\/mike-nichols\/","widget_id":"AR_6","hide":false}},{"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3583780\/princess-diana-history\/","shortlink":"http:\/\/wp.me\/p5HMd-f2iU","title":"The Princess Diana TV Interview That Made History","friendly_title":"The Princess Diana TV Interview That Made History","post_type":"post","available":true,"time_article":true,"comments_allowed":true,"short_title":"The Princess Diana TV Interview That Made History","excerpt":"Nov. 20, 1995: Princess Diana admits, during a TV interview, that she had an affair with her riding instructor","format":"article","time":{"pretty":"Nov. 20, 2014","published":"2014-11-20 10:30:26","updated":"2014-11-20 15:30:26","minute":"10:30 am","short":"11\/20"},"authors":[{"id":262496150,"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/author\/jennifer-latson\/","name":"Jennifer Latson","bio":"","short_bio":"","types":["contributor"],"twitter":"JennieLatson","twitter_url":"https:\/\/twitter.com\/JennieLatson","gplus":"","fb":"","email":"","thumbnail":null,"contributor":false}],"content":"<aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-related\" data-name=\"rr-related\"><div class=\"read-more-inline related\"><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/99288\/grace-of-monaco-vs-diana-which-princess-received-the-bigger-flop\/\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-article data-event=\"rr-related\"><img src=\"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/05\/diana-naomi-watts-grace-monaco-nicole-kidman.jpg?w=560&#038;h=374&#038;crop=1\" alt=\"From left: Naomi Watts as Princess Diana in Diana, and Nicole Kidman as Princess Grace in Grace of Monaco.\" title=\"From left: Naomi Watts as Princess Diana in &lt;i&gt;Diana&lt;\/i&gt;, and Nicole Kidman as Princess Grace in &lt;i&gt;Grace of Monaco&lt;\/i&gt;.\"><h6 class=\"read-more-list-h\">More<\/h6><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title\"><i>Grace of Monaco<\/i> vs. <i>Diana<\/i>: Which Princess Biopic Is More Disastrous?<\/h3><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/71779\/kate-middleton-prince-william-australia-diana-charles\/\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-article data-event=\"rr-related\"><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title\">Kate and William Recreate Photo of Diana and Charles Three Decades Later<\/h3><\/a><\/div><\/aside><p>The infidelity itself was hardly news, but when Princess Diana admitted on British TV that she had been unfaithful to Prince Charles, it &ldquo;<a href=\"http:\/\/www.people.com\/people\/archive\/article\/0,,20102272,00.html\">plunged the monarchy into the greatest crisis since the Abdication<\/a>,&rdquo; the <em>Daily Mail <\/em>said, referencing King Edward VIII&rsquo;s 1936 <a href=\"http:\/\/www.royal.gov.uk\/historyofthemonarchy\/kingsandqueensoftheunitedkingdom\/thehouseofwindsor\/edwardviii.aspx\">abandonment of his throne<\/a> to marry a divorced American socialite.<\/p>\n<aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-partner\" data-name=\"rr-partner\"><div class=\"read-more-list\"><h6 class=\"read-more-list-h\">More<\/h6><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/storyline\/michael-brown-shooting\/pair-suspected-trying-acquire-bombs-ferguson-protests-n254021?cid=par-time_20141122\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">Feds Suspect Pair Sought Bombs for Ferguson Protests <span>NBC News<\/span><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/news\/crime-courts\/ohio-men-wrongly-convicted-murder-after-39-years-released-n253356?cid=par-time_20141122\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">Two Ohio Men Wrongly Convicted of Murder Walk Free <span>NBC News<\/span><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/news\/us-news\/fsu-shooter-myron-may-left-message-i-do-not-want-n253436?cid=par-time_20141122\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">FSU Shooter Left Message: 'I Do Not Want to Die in Vain' <span>NBC News<\/span><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.huffingtonpost.ca\/2014\/11\/20\/maple-leafs-american-anthem_n_6193658.html\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">Toronto Maple Leafs Fans Sing National Anthem After Microphone Fails <span>Huffington Post<\/span><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.huffingtonpost.com\/2014\/11\/19\/golden-retriever-dog-fails-obedience-test-video_n_6186890.html\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">Watch This Golden Retriever Go On A Delightful Rampage During Obedience Competition <span>Huffington Post<\/span><\/a><\/div><\/aside><p>On this day, Nov. 20, in 1995, the BBC aired Diana&rsquo;s <a href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=BjYU7Q7hqEI\">first solo press interview<\/a> &mdash; a stroke of independence made possible by keeping her meeting with BBC&rsquo;s Martin Bashir <a href=\"http:\/\/www.people.com\/people\/archive\/article\/0,,20102272,00.html\">secret from Buckingham Palace<\/a>. She took the opportunity to address the tensions within her marriage, her struggles with postpartum depression and bulimia, and the fact that she had been intimately involved with a man other than the Prince.<\/p>\n<p>Charles had admitted <a href=\"http:\/\/www.nytimes.com\/1994\/06\/30\/world\/prince-charles-in-tv-documentary-admits-to-infidelity.html\">to his own infidelity<\/a> on a TV documentary the previous year. His longtime affair with Camilla Parker Bowles was no secret when Diana told Bashir, &ldquo;There were three of us in this marriage, so it was a bit crowded.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Rumors of her five-year affair with cavalry officer James Hewitt, whom she&rsquo;d hired as a riding instructor, had already made news as well, partly because he&rsquo;d profited from the story by collaborating on a tell-all book, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.people.com\/people\/archive\/article\/0,,20104143,00.html\"><em>Princess in Love<\/em><\/a>. In the interview, Diana said, &ldquo;Yes, I adored him. Yes, I was in love with him. But I was very let down.&rdquo;<\/p>\n<p>In her surprise that Hewitt betrayed her, some saw the same na&iuml;vet&eacute; that a young Diana, barely out of her teens, had worn like a veil on her wedding day. Following Diana&rsquo;s death in a 1997 car crash, <a href=\"http:\/\/content.time.com\/time\/subscriber\/article\/0,33009,986982-1,00.html\">Joyce Carol Oates wrote an essay<\/a> for TIME in which she linked &ldquo;the drama in the princess&rsquo;s life&rdquo; to &ldquo;her often desperate search for love&rdquo; and her utter devastation when her husband failed her. Oates wrote:<\/p><div class=\"content-ad\" id=\"content-ad-3583780\"><\/div>\n<blockquote><p>Of Diana at the time of the wedding, it was said by a former classmate that she was &#8220;one of the few virgins of her age around. She was a complete romantic, and she was saving herself for the love of her life, which she knew would come one day.&#8221; There is no evidence that Diana would have behaved other than devotedly to her husband and family if she hadn&#8217;t been forced to acknowledge that her husband wasn&#8217;t only having a clandestine affair with another man&#8217;s wife, but had been having this affair for years.<\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p>By the early 1990s, when Charles and Diana were already leading separate lives, a biography of Diana revealed that, just a year after her wedding, she had <a href=\"http:\/\/content.time.com\/time\/magazine\/article\/0,9171,986949-5,00.html\">attempted suicide<\/a> over her suspicions about Charles&rsquo; relationship with Camilla. On a 1985 visit to a London hospice, <a href=\"http:\/\/content.time.com\/time\/magazine\/article\/0,9171,986949-5,00.html\">according to TIME<\/a>, &ldquo;she let slip a telling comment. &lsquo;The biggest disease this world suffers from,&rsquo; she complained, &lsquo;[is] people feeling unloved.&rsquo; &rdquo;<\/p>\n<p>That was no excuse for airing dirty laundry, however &mdash; at least not to the Royal Family. Within a month of Diana&rsquo;s interview, her press secretary had resigned and the Queen had sent Charles and Diana <a href=\"http:\/\/www.nytimes.com\/1995\/12\/21\/world\/queen-urges-prince-charles-and-diana-to-divorce-soon.html\">a letter urging them to divorce quickly<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><em><strong>Read the 1997 special report on Diana&#8217;s death, here in the TIME Vault<\/strong><\/em>: Death of a Princess<\/p><aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-ad\" data-name=\"rr-ad\"><div class=\"right-rail-ad\" id=\"right-rail-ad-3583780\"><\/div><\/aside><aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-share\" data-name=\"rr-share\"><span class=\"social-links\">\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-mail social-link-mail\" href=\"mailto:?subject=The%20Princess%20Diana%20TV%20Interview%20That%20Made%20History%20%7C%20TIME&body=The%20Princess%20Diana%20TV%20Interview%20That%20Made%20History%0A%0ANov.%2020%2C%201995%3A%20Princess%20Diana%20admits%2C%20during%20a%20TV%20interview%2C%20that%20she%20had%20an%20affair%20with%20her%20riding%20instructor%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3583780%2Fprincess-diana-history%2F\" data-event=\"email\" title=\"Click to Email this article\"><\/a>\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-fb social-link-fb popup\" href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/sharer\/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3583780%2Fprincess-diana-history%2F\" data-event=\"fb-share\" title=\"Click to post this article to Facebook\"><\/a>\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-tw social-link-tw popup\" href=\"#\" data-href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwp.me%2Fp5HMd-f2iU&text=Nov.%2020%2C%201995%3A%20Princess%20Diana%20admits%2C%20during%20a%20TV%20interview%2C%20that%20she%20had%20an%20affair%20with%20her%20riding%20instructor&via=TIMEHistory\" data-event=\"tweet\" title=\"Click to Tweet this article\"><\/a>\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-linkedin social-link-linkedin popup\" href=\"http:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/shareArticle?mini=true&url=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3583780%2Fprincess-diana-history%2F&title=The+Princess+Diana+TV+Interview+That+Made+History\" data-event=\"linkedin\" title=\"Click to post this article to LinkedIn\"><\/a>\n    <a href=\"#\" class=\"time-icons time-icons-comment toggle-comments\" data-lf-site-id=\"314099\" data-lf-article-id=\"3583780\" data-url=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3583780\/princess-diana-history\/\" data-title=\"The Princess Diana TV Interview That Made History\" title=\"Click to view and post comments\" data-event=\"comment-click\">0<\/a>\n<\/span>\n<\/aside>","section":{"name":"History","slug":"history","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/history\/","description":"The news in context, from the archives of TIME. A historical view on breaking news, entertainment, media coverage, anniversaries, births, deaths and more"},"hero":{"class":"landscape","thumbnail":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/11\/diana-bashir.jpeg?w=100&h=100&crop=1","src":{"small":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/11\/diana-bashir.jpeg?w=280","small_2x":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/11\/diana-bashir.jpeg?w=560","large":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/11\/diana-bashir.jpeg?w=550","large_2x":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/11\/diana-bashir.jpeg?w=1100"},"credit":"AFP \/ Getty Images","caption":"The Princess of Wales is interviewed by the BBC's Martin Bashir (R) on Nov. 20, 1995","alt":"Princess Diana and Martin Bashir","providers":[]},"id":3583780,"encoded_url":"http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3583780%2Fprincess-diana-history%2F","encoded_shortlink":"http%3A%2F%2Fwp.me%2Fp5HMd-f2iU","encoded_title":"The+Princess+Diana+TV+Interview+That+Made+History","twitter_text":"Nov.%2020%2C%201995%3A%20Princess%20Diana%20admits%2C%20during%20a%20TV%20interview%2C%20that%20she%20had%20an%20affair%20with%20her%20riding%20instructor","twitter_via":"TIMEHistory","related_posts":[{"id":99288,"title":"<i>Grace of Monaco<\/i> vs. <i>Diana<\/i>: Which Princess Biopic Is More Disastrous?","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/99288\/grace-of-monaco-vs-diana-which-princess-received-the-bigger-flop\/","format":"article","paid":false,"edit_link":null,"contributor":false,"short_title":"<i>Grace of Monaco<\/i> vs. <i>Diana<\/i>: Which Princess Biopic Is More Disastrous?","hero":{"class":"landscape","thumbnail":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/05\/diana-naomi-watts-grace-monaco-nicole-kidman.jpg?w=100&h=100&crop=1","src":{"small":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/05\/diana-naomi-watts-grace-monaco-nicole-kidman.jpg?w=280&h=187&crop=1","small_2x":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/05\/diana-naomi-watts-grace-monaco-nicole-kidman.jpg?w=560&h=374&crop=1","large":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/05\/diana-naomi-watts-grace-monaco-nicole-kidman.jpg?w=550&h=367&crop=1","large_2x":"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/05\/diana-naomi-watts-grace-monaco-nicole-kidman.jpg?w=1100&h=734&crop=1"},"credit":"Laurie Sparham\u2014Entertainment One; David Koskas\u2014Weinstein Company","caption":"From left: Naomi Watts as Princess Diana in <i>Diana<\/i>, and Nicole Kidman as Princess Grace in <i>Grace of Monaco<\/i>.","alt":"From left: Naomi Watts as Princess Diana in Diana, and Nicole Kidman as Princess Grace in Grace of Monaco.","providers":[]}},{"id":71779,"title":"Kate and William Recreate Photo of Diana and Charles Three Decades Later","url":"http:\/\/time.com\/71779\/kate-middleton-prince-william-australia-diana-charles\/","format":"article","paid":false,"edit_link":null,"contributor":false,"short_title":"Kate and William Recreate Photo of Diana and Charles Three Decades Later"}],"subjects":[null],"ads":{"neg":"false","post_title":"The Princess Diana TV Interview That Made History"},"Partner_Module":{"partner":"Select","post_title":"The Princess Diana TV Interview That Made History"},"email_title":"The%20Princess%20Diana%20TV%20Interview%20That%20Made%20History%20%7C%20TIME","email_body":"The%20Princess%20Diana%20TV%20Interview%20That%20Made%20History%0A%0ANov.%2020%2C%201995%3A%20Princess%20Diana%20admits%2C%20during%20a%20TV%20interview%2C%20that%20she%20had%20an%20affair%20with%20her%20riding%20instructor%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3583780%2Fprincess-diana-history%2F","omniture":{"modules":"rr-related|rr-partner|rr-ad|rr-share"},"outbrain":{"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3583780\/princess-diana-history\/","widget_id":"AR_6","hide":false}},{"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/3596016\/smoking-news-history\/","shortlink":"http:\/\/wp.me\/p5HMd-f5ug","title":"Smoking News to Make You Cringe","friendly_title":"Smoking News to Make You Cringe","post_type":"post","available":true,"time_article":true,"comments_allowed":true,"short_title":"Smoking News to Make You Cringe","excerpt":"Read TIME's reports from the era when the medical community thought it was O.K. to smoke","format":"article","time":{"pretty":"Nov. 20, 2014","published":"2014-11-20 09:00:36","updated":"2014-11-20 14:00:36","minute":"9:00 am","short":"11\/20"},"authors":[{"id":207020909,"url":"http:\/\/time.com\/author\/alexandra-sifferlin\/","name":"Alexandra Sifferlin","bio":"Alexandra Sifferlin is a reporter for TIME covering all things health-related. She is a graduate from the Northwestern University Medill School of Journalism.","short_bio":"","types":[],"twitter":"acsifferlin","twitter_url":"https:\/\/twitter.com\/acsifferlin","gplus":"110376986433078721859","fb":"","email":"","thumbnail":"http:\/\/i1.wp.com\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/01\/mg_1589.jpg?crop=441px%2C168px%2C2423px%2C2422px&resize=100%2C100","contributor":false}],"content":"<aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-related\" data-name=\"rr-related\"><div class=\"read-more-inline related\"><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3478135\/smoking-drinking-hpv\/\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-article data-event=\"rr-related\"><img src=\"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/10\/smoking-lit-cigarette.jpg?w=560\" alt=\"smoking lit cigarette\" title=\"\"><h6 class=\"read-more-list-h\">More<\/h6><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title\">Smoking and Drinking Raise Your Risk for Oral HPV<\/h3><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3403784\/marlboro-boys-photographing-underage-smoking-in-indonesia\/\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-gallery data-event=\"rr-related\"><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title\">&#8216;Marlboro Boys&#8217;: Photographing Underage Smoking in Indonesia<\/h3><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3374941\/quitting-smoking\/\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-brief data-event=\"rr-related\"><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title\">Here&#8217;s the Best Way to Get Someone to Quit Smoking<\/h3><\/a><\/div><\/aside><p>Thursday marks the American Cancer Society&#8217;s <a href=\"http:\/\/www.cancer.org\/healthy\/stayawayfromtobacco\/greatamericansmokeout\/index\" target=\"_blank\">Great American Smokeout<\/a> (GASO), a nationwide event encouraging smokers to kick the habit.<\/p>\n<aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-partner\" data-name=\"rr-partner\"><div class=\"read-more-list\"><h6 class=\"read-more-list-h\">More<\/h6><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3598444\/lancet-violence-against-women-global\/\" class=\"read-more-list-article\" data-event=\"rr-more\">New Global Study Calls Violence Against Women &#8216;Epidemic&#8217;<\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3598285\/transgender-lifeline-help-line\/\" class=\"read-more-list-article\" data-event=\"rr-more\">New Crisis Line Aims to Help Transgender People at Risk of Suicide<\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/storyline\/michael-brown-shooting\/pair-suspected-trying-acquire-bombs-ferguson-protests-n254021?cid=par-time_20141122\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">Feds Suspect Pair Sought Bombs for Ferguson Protests <span>NBC News<\/span><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/news\/crime-courts\/ohio-men-wrongly-convicted-murder-after-39-years-released-n253356?cid=par-time_20141122\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">Two Ohio Men Wrongly Convicted of Murder Walk Free <span>NBC News<\/span><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/www.nbcnews.com\/news\/us-news\/fsu-shooter-myron-may-left-message-i-do-not-want-n253436?cid=par-time_20141122\" class=\"read-more-partner-article\" data-event=\"rr-partner\" target=\"_blank\">FSU Shooter Left Message: 'I Do Not Want to Die in Vain' <span>NBC News<\/span><\/a><\/div><\/aside><p>We know today that cigarette smoking causes serious diseases in every organ of the body, including lung cancer, diabetes, colorectal and liver cancer, rheumatoid arthritis, erectile dysfunction, age-related macular degeneration, and more. Tobacco use rakes up more than $96 billion a year in medical costs, and it&#8217;s <a href=\"http:\/\/www.cdc.gov\/tobacco\/data_statistics\/fact_sheets\/adult_data\/cig_smoking\/index.htm\" target=\"_blank\">estimated<\/a> that 42.1 million people, or 18.1% of all adults in the U.S. smoke cigarettes.<\/p>\n<aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-mag\" data-name=\"rr-mag\"><div class=\"read-more-inline magazine has-cover\"><h6 class=\"read-more-list-h read-more-popular\">Popular Among Subscribers<\/h6>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"popular-lead\"><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3547827\/the-art-of-science\/?pcd=pw-pas\"><img src=\"http:\/\/timedotcom.files.wordpress.com\/2014\/10\/timeinterstellarcover.jpg?w=560\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" data-loaded=\"true\"><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3547827\/the-art-of-science\/?pcd=pw-pas\" class=\"read-more-article\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title time-icons time-icons-key\"><em>Interstellar<\/em>, Where No Movie Has Gone Before<\/h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/subscription.time.com\/storefront\/subscribe-to-time\/link\/1019509.html\" class=\"subscribe-button\">Subscribe<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3547825\/nucor-tries-to-reverse-decline-in-american-steelmaking\/?pcd=pw-pas\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-article><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title time-icons time-icons-key\">The Last Men of Steel<\/h3><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/3547828\/review-interstellar-christopher-nolan\/?pcd=pw-pas\" class=\"read-more-article\" format-article><h3 class=\"read-more-inline-title time-icons time-icons-key\">Review: <em>Interstellar\u2019s<\/em> Wonder of Worlds Beyond<\/h3><\/a><\/div><\/aside><p>This year marked the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.cdc.gov\/tobacco\/data_statistics\/sgr\/50th-anniversary\/index.htm\" target=\"_blank\">50th anniversary<\/a> of the historic 1964 Surgeon General&rsquo;s report that concluded that smoking caused lung cancer, and should be avoided. Before then, smoking messaging was depressingly inaccurate. Despite concerns &mdash; initially from a small minority of medical experts &mdash; the tobacco industry boomed in the U.S., and even doctors considered the effects of cigarettes to be benign.<\/p>\n<p>Here are some examples of tobacco-related beliefs that appeared through the years in TIME Magazine:<\/p>\n<p><strong>1923: <\/strong>In <a href=\"http:\/\/content.time.com\/time\/subscriber\/article\/0,33009,727333-1,00.html\" target=\"_blank\">an article<\/a> about a recent compilation of smoking-related data, TIME was mostly concerned with whether smoking made people more or less brainy: &#8220;The outstanding fact of this survey is that every man in the literary group smokes, and the majority of the literary women. Moreover, most of them consider its effects beneficial, and claim that their literary and imaginative powers are stimulated by it.&#8221; And later: &#8220;From the laboratory data, the author concludes that it is impossible to say that tobacco smoking will retard the intellectual processes of any one person, but in a large group it may be predicted that the majority will be slightly retarded.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p><strong>1928:<\/strong> Some experts tried early on to warn about the effect of nicotine, but were met with resistance. In <a href=\"http:\/\/content.time.com\/time\/subscriber\/article\/0,33009,881157,00.html\" target=\"_blank\">an article<\/a> about a researcher presenting data on nicotine and the brain, TIME writes: &#8220;Many U. S. doctors have contended and often hoped to prove that smoking does no harm. In Newark, N. J., five children of the Fillimon family have been smoking full-sized cigars since the age of two. The oldest, Frank, 11, now averages five cigars a day. All of these children appear healthy, go to school regularly, get good grades.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p><strong>1935:<\/strong> Questions <a href=\"http:\/\/content.time.com\/time\/subscriber\/article\/0,33009,748485,00.html\" target=\"_blank\">began<\/a> to be raised about the effects on infants, though uptake was limited: &#8220;Physiologists agree that smoking does no more harm to a woman than to a man, if harm there be. According to many investigators, the only circumstances under which a woman should not smoke are while she has anesthetic gas in her lungs (she might explode), and while she produces milk for her baby. Milk drains from the blood of a smoking mother those smoke ingredients which please her, but may not agree with her nursling.&#8221;<\/p><div class=\"content-ad\" id=\"content-ad-3596016\"><\/div>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>1938<\/strong> Even if there might be adverse health events for some smokers,<a href=\"http:\/\/content.time.com\/time\/subscriber\/article\/0,33009,883715,00.html\" target=\"_blank\"> not all physicians agreed<\/a> it was a universal risk: <\/span>&#8220;In step with a recent upsurge of articles on smoking, in the current issue of Scribner&#8217;s, Mr. Furnas offers several anti-smoking aids for what they are worth. Samples: 1) wash out the mouth with a weak solution of silver nitrate which &#8216;makes a smoke taste as if it had been cured in sour milk&#8217;; 2) chew candied ginger, gentian, or camomile; 3) to occupy the hands smoke a prop cigaret. For many a smoker, however, this facetious advice may be unnecessary, since many a doctor has come to the conclusion that, no matter what else it may do to you, smoking does not injure the heart of a healthy person.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>1949: <\/strong><\/span>By the late 1940s, smoking had become a <a href=\"http:\/\/content.time.com\/time\/subscriber\/article\/0,33009,853667,00.html\" target=\"_blank\">contentious debate<\/a> in the medical community: &#8220;Smoking? Possibly a minor cause of cancer of the mouth, said Dr. MacDonald. But smoking, argued New Orleans&#8217; Dr. Alton Ochsner, can be blamed for the increase of cancer of the lung. Surgeon Ochsner, a nonsmoker, was positive. Dr. Charles S. Cameron, A.C.S. medical and scientific director, who does smoke, was not so sure. For every expert who blames tobacco for the increase of cancer of the lung, he said, there is another who says tobacco is not the cause.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>1962<\/strong> More evidence was linking tobacco to cancer, and some groups were trying to get pregnant women to quit out of potential risks to the child, <a href=\"http:\/\/content.time.com\/time\/subscriber\/article\/0,33009,870054,00.html\" target=\"_blank\">but still<\/a>: <\/span>&#8220;Some doctors, though, see no direct connection between smoking and prematurity; they argue that the problem is a matter of temperament, that high-strung women who smoke would have a high proportion of &#8220;preemies&#8221; anyway.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p><span class=\"s1\"><strong>1964<\/strong> In a historic move, the 1964 Surgeon General&#8217;s report officially stated that cigarette smoking causes cancer, giving authority to anti-smoking campaigns. TIME <a href=\"http:\/\/content.time.com\/time\/subscriber\/article\/0,33009,875592,00.html\" target=\"_blank\">wrote<\/a>: <\/span><\/p>\n<blockquote><p>The conclusion was just about what everybody had expected. &#8220;On the basis of prolonged study and evaluation,&#8221; the 150,000-word report declared, &#8220;the committee makes the following judgment: Cigarette smoking is a health hazard of sufficient importance in the U.S. to warrant appropriate remedial action.&#8221; More significant than the words was their source: it was the unanimous report of an impartial committee of top experts in several health fields, backed by the full authority of the U.S. Government.<\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p><em><strong>Read TIME&#8217;s full 1964 coverage of the Surgeon General&#8217;s report, here in the TIME Vault: <\/strong><\/em><a href=\"http:\/\/time.com\/vault\/issue\/1964-01-17\/page\/50\/\" target=\"_blank\">The Government Report<\/a><\/p><aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-ad\" data-name=\"rr-ad\"><div class=\"right-rail-ad\" id=\"right-rail-ad-3596016\"><\/div><\/aside><aside class=\"right-rail-module rr-share\" data-name=\"rr-share\"><span class=\"social-links\">\n    <a class=\"time-icons time-icons-mail social-link-mail\" href=\"mailto:?subject=Smoking%20News%20to%20Make%20You%20Cringe%20%7C%20TIME&body=Smoking%20News%20to%20Make%20You%20Cringe%0A%0ARead%20TIME%27s%20reports%20from%20the%20era%20when%20the%20medical%20community%20thought%20it%20was%20O.K.%20to%20smoke%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftim